I will fix the "Network Error" by refactoring the network layer to use a **Proxy Strategy**.

**The Technical Problem:**
Currently, the frontend is trying to connect directly to the Railway backend (`https://...`) from your browser. This triggers **CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing)** security checks, which often fail in Cloud IDEs due to mismatched domains or cookie policies, resulting in a "Network Error".

**The Solution:**
I will configure the frontend to send requests to itself (`/api`). The Vite Development Server will then intercept these requests and forward them to the Railway backend. This happens server-to-server, completely bypassing browser CORS restrictions.

I will also remove the `importmap` from `index.html` which is causing script conflicts, and add a safety check to the backend to prevent crashes if the database is empty.

